label: ABC Records
notes:
Printed inner sleeve.

This was also "re-issued" as part of the MCA budget series in the early 80's, but it doesn't appear any new copies were pressed with the new catalog number of new labels. Instead, warehouse copies of this original issue were stamped in gold on front with "MCA-700" and barcode with the new information was slapped on the back cover (barcode on shrinkwrap on the back 0 000030 540941.) These should be treated as part of the original issue.

Recorded in July and August, 1978 at Hollywood Sound Recorders, Inc.

Mastered at A&M Recording Studios, Los Angeles.

notes:
"Through the ages, the peacock has been honored and praised dor its attractive, illustrious beauty. Of all the bird family, the peacock is the only bird that integrates all colors into one, and displays this radiance of fire only when in love."
"We, like the peacock, try to integrate all races into through the love of music."
-Michael and Jackie Jackson For Peacock Productions.

Sticker to shrinkwrap states "Anti Loudness / Studio Master Tamotsu Yoshida / The Ultimate Sound to Revive Analog Presence".

NB: Insert includes miscredited writing of track five to Gene Page. This was corrected on later issues.

title_release: You Can't Win (Part 1) / You Can't Win (Part 2)
notes:
Music from the Motown musical motion picture "The Wiz". Michael Jackson's role in this adaption of "The Wizard Of Oz" with an all african-american cast was the scare crow. 
The full version of this song is on cd available on The Ultimate Collection, or the limited australian 50th anniversary edition of "King Of Pop".

It says 2:48 on the label but it actually runs 2:58 like the 12" release.
